1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO TAXATION; EXTENDING THE PROPERTY TAX EXEMPTION
3 PERIOD FOR PROJECT PROPERTY IN METROPOLITAN REDEVELOPMENT
4 AREAS.
5
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
7 SECTION 1. Section 3-60A-13.1 NMSA 1978 (being Laws
8 1985, Chapter 225, Section 2, as amended) is amended to read:
9 "3-60A-13.1. PAYMENTS IN LIEU OF PROPERTY TAXES AND
10 ASSESSMENTS.--
11 A. If interests in project property are exempt
12 from property taxation and assessments under Subsection B of
13 Section 3-60A-13 NMSA 1978 or Section 7-36-3.1 NMSA 1978,
14 then during the period extending from the date of acquisition
15 of the property by the local government through December 31
16 of a year that shall not exceed the fourteenth anniversary of
17 that acquisition date, any lessee of the project property or
18 owner of a substantial beneficial interest in the project
19 property, in whose ownership the property would not be
20 exempt from property taxation except for the exemption
21 granted under Section 7-36-3.1 NMSA 1978, shall pay to the
22 county treasurer annually, at the same time property tax
23 payments are due under the Property Tax Code, an amount equal
24 to the sum of:
25 (1) general property taxes that would have SB 58
