1 been imposed under Subsection B of Section 7-37-7 NMSA 1978
2 had it not been exempt and had it been valued at the
3 valuation for property taxation purposes that existed in the
4 year immediately preceding the year of acquisition by the
5 local government;
6 (2) amounts that would have been imposed
7 under Subsection C of Section 7-37-7 NMSA 1978 on the project
8 property had it not been exempt and had it been valued at the
9 valuation for property taxation purposes that existed in the
10 year immediately preceding the year of acquisition by the
11 local government; and
12 (3) amounts that would have been imposed as
13 benefit assessments on the project property had it not been
14 exempt and had it been valued at the valuation for property
15 taxation purposes that existed in the year immediately
16 preceding the year of acquisition by the local government if
those benefit assessments are authorized by law and are
17
expressed in mills per dollar or dollars per thousand dollars
18
of net taxable value of property, assessed value of property
19
or similar terms.
20
B. The county treasurer shall distribute all
21
amounts collected under Subsection A of this section in the
22
same manner as the amounts would have been distributed if
23
they had been collected as taxes or assessments on nonexempt
24
property.
25 SB 58
