1 C. The provisions of this section shall apply only
2 to project property acquired by a local government under the
3 provisions of the Metropolitan Redevelopment Code on or after
4 January 1, 1986."
5 SECTION 2. Section 7-36-3.1 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 1979,
6 Chapter 56, Section 2, as amended) is amended to read:
7 "7-36-3.1. METROPOLITAN REDEVELOPMENT PROPERTY--TAX
8 STATUS OF LESSEE'S INTERESTS.--Property interests of a lessee
9 in project property held under a lease with respect to a
10 project authorized by the Metropolitan Redevelopment Code and
11 acquired or held by a municipality prior to January 1, 1986
12 under the provisions of that code are exempt from property
13 taxation for as long as there is an outstanding bonded
14 indebtedness, but in any event for a period not to exceed
15 fourteen years from the date of execution of the first lease
16 of the project by the municipality. Property interests of a
lessee of or an owner of a substantial beneficial interest in
17
project property acquired or held by a municipality on or
18
after January 1, 1986 with respect to a project authorized by
19
the Metropolitan Redevelopment Code are exempt from property
20
taxation for a period extending from the date of acquisition
21
of the project property by the municipality through December
22
31 of a year that shall not exceed the fourteenth anniversary
23
of that acquisition date."
24
